        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-23T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="562" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d562">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">859.01/2–2145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-23T20:00:00-04:00">February 23, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>341. In view of the information contained in your 658, February 21, 8 p.m.,
                    Ambassador Harriman is not being requested to approach the Soviet authorities at
                    this time regarding the message from the Freedom Council and political party
                    leaders. Department feels that this decision should not, however, occasion a
                    further delay in the delivery of our acknowledgment to the Council and the party
                    leaders. You are therefore requested to transmit it to Foss and Munck at your
                    earliest convenience.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
